		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				1) Can you make our Guild Name UNDER our Avatar name instead of having a 'book' go across our head please? <br>  <br> 2) We have all seen players run around with some outfits that just dont look very pleasing to your avatar. You have these really nice arms and legs, but everything else looks like it came from the Army and Navy store. Think we can add a Merchant who we can choose dye colors from to at least match our armors to? <br>  <br> 3) Help those people who live in Full-Screen mode only. Make a new version of the spell book where we can choose our spells IN full-screen, like looking at our inventory, etc. Why we must go into that god-aweful 'grey' screen look to pick our spells all the time, I will never know.  <br>  <br> 4) When you die, you are mostly looking for a res, and attempting to go loot your corpse naked across Skyfire, and our items is what MAKES our character (sigh). We get hit, bam bam bam, dead again. Could we possibly make it so when you die, you appear at your bind spot with your inventory/armor on you? If it was not for the fact that the stats on our items is what makes your character, I wouldnt mind it so much. This would lessen the time for people just waiting around playing gems looking for resses forever. Instead they can still go off and hunt while waiting for a res, or perhaps off fighting somewhere and forgetting about your corpse. <br>  <br> 5) New trade skill additions. To make the economy more healthy, people who can make armor, jewelry, etc should be more of a priority than most. Add more items that you can make at a lower level or level cost as well as putting more vendors in the same area so you dont have to 'port' to 10 zones over, then 'port' back to make something. What about those people who cant port at all? <br>  <br> 6) Being &quot;EverQuest&quot;, I fail to see why we dont have a &quot;Quest Log&quot;. I decided to continue my epic (laugh) and forgot where I was in the quest.  <br>  <br> Thanks for reading, hope this turns on a few lightbulbs of ideas. <br>  <br> 		

