			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Beuatiful post, Bastian and all true.  A couple of other points I'd like to throw in... <br>  <br> 1) Expense:  I don't know how it is on whichever server you play on, but getting decent gear for you level is just astronomical on mine.  I walked through the auction zone the other night and saw a Heavy Dragonhide BP selling for 100,000 plat.  That's the most expensive thing I've seen so far, but after the Treeweave BP...  expect to fork over 30k+ for an upgrade. <br>  <br> 2) Getting Money:  Have you ever noticed that if you play anything besides say a Druid or a Cleric with an XP rez money is hard to come by?  You can't make cash on tradeskills.  At least not on my server.  The only real way to make money is to head to places like Seb or KC or Velks and get in one of the &quot;good&quot; camps, win the roll of an item, and then run to the auction zone and sit for a few hours trying to sell it. <br>  <br> 3) Getting a Group:  This one is kind of iffy as I know many people (most either a chanter or a cleric) who have no problems at all getting a group.  Unfortunatly for me...  I play a rogue.  I love the class, but it's nearly impossible to get a group.  I've sat in places like Seb and Velks for over 3 hours /oocing for a group with no response.  I can't solo effectively without spending large ammounts of cash on non-stackable poisons and even then it's -real- chancy. <br>  <br> 4) &quot;Uber&quot; Guilds:  It seems to me that Verant is catering to the &quot;uber&quot; guilds lately.  Especially with the Vellious expansion.  Unless you belong to one of the huge guilds...  What are your chances of getting any of the vellious quest armors?  Doing the Coldain Ring Quest?  Hunting in Veeshan's Peak or even Western Wastes?  Answer:  About as likely as finding a lemonade stand in..  well, you know where. <br>  <br> These are some of the things that are seriously causing me to think of dropping my EQ account in favor of that &quot;other game&quot; that has already figured out ways around most of this.  I love EQ, and like the originator of this post... I've been playing since shortly after it came out.  EQ was way ahead of it's time when it came out, but it's beginning to show it's age.  It needs some changes, and I'm not talking about more expansions.		

