				You have some good points and some bad ones. Overall I think your really nitpicking. <br>  <br> 1. Moving the guild name is a good idea. <br>  <br> 2. We dont need dye. If you want a matching set get a full set. I dont want players to be able to dye their crappy armor and have the same look as my high level quest/plane armor. <br>  <br> 3. Ok idea but not needed. After med gets to a decent level it only takes a matter of seconds to mem a spell. <br>  <br> 4. Very bad idea. CR is not supposed to be fun. Its supposed to suck so death actually means something. Death in AO and DAOC is so easy theirs no tension. You are never actually scared of dieing because it just dont matter much. Being scared of dieing is fun, easy death penelties make a boring game. You shouldn't die that much anyway or your doing something wrong. At mid level up you nearly always have a Cleric in your group. If you choose to solo you must understand it has its own risks accociated with it. 90+ % exp res's are easy to get. Clerics always need money and theres tons of em on every server between 50-60.  <br>  <br> 5. Its always better to have more trade skills . Their all pretty boring though to most people. Not many people find sitting around for hours combining stuff fun. <br>  <br> 6. A quest log would be cool. Of course you could just write the stuff down. I'm sure you printed your epic info from a web page to begin with.		

